# 🤖 LangChain Q&A Chatbot — OpenAI + Streamlit

A modular **AI-powered Question & Answer chatbot** built using **LangChain**, **OpenAI GPT models**, and **Streamlit**.
This application enables users to interact with a Large Language Model (LLM) through a simple web interface and receive intelligent, real-time responses.

This project follows a clean, scalable architecture suitable for **GenAI portfolio projects and production-ready applications**.

---

## 📌 Features

* Real-time AI question answering using OpenAI LLM
* Interactive Streamlit web interface
* Secure API key management using `.env`
* Lightweight and fast implementation
* Clean and modular architecture

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

### Backend

* Python 3.x
* LangChain
* OpenAI API
* Python-dotenv

### Frontend

* Streamlit

### LLM

* OpenAI GPT-4o-mini (via LangChain)

---

## 🏗️ Architecture

```
👤 User enters question in Streamlit UI
        ↓
🌐 Streamlit sends request to LangChain
        ↓
🤖 LangChain invokes OpenAI GPT model
        ↓
🧠 OpenAI generates intelligent response
        ↓
📤 Response returned to Streamlit
        ↓
💬 Displayed to user in web interface
```

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```
langchain/
│
└── qna/
    │
    ├── app.py               # Streamlit application entry point
    ├── requirements.txt    # Project dependencies
    ├── README.md           # Documentation
    └── .env                # Environment variables (not committed)
```

---

## ⚡ Key Components

| Component          | Description                         |
| ------------------ | ----------------------------------- |
| Streamlit UI       | Interactive frontend for user input |
| LangChain          | LLM orchestration framework         |
| ChatOpenAI         | OpenAI GPT model integration        |
| Environment Config | Secure API key management           |
| Response Handler   | Processes and displays responses    |

---

## 🔑 Environment Variables

Create a `.env` file in the `qna` folder:

```
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here
```

Get your API key from:
[https://platform.openai.com/api-keys](https://platform.openai.com/api-keys)

---

## 🚀 Running Locally

### 1️⃣ Clone the repository

```
git clone https://github.com/saznashaik/langchain.git

cd langchain/qna
```

---

### 2️⃣ Create virtual environment

```
python -m venv venv
```

Activate environment:

**Windows**

```
venv\Scripts\activate
```

**Mac/Linux**

```
source venv/bin/activate
```

---

### 3️⃣ Install dependencies

```
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

### 4️⃣ Run the application

```
streamlit run app.py
```

---

### 5️⃣ Access in browser

```
http://localhost:8501
```

---

## 📡 Application Flow

```
User Question
     ↓
Streamlit UI
     ↓
LangChain
     ↓
OpenAI GPT Model
     ↓
Generated Response
     ↓
Displayed to User
```

